COROLLARY.

But it ought here opportunely to be observed, nothing will fail in the argument made, although the angle at the point L is assumed right, together with hypothesis of acute angle. For still that common perpendicular LK would be less (from Cor. I. to P. III.) than the other perpendicular HK, from which therefore still a portion MK could be assumed equal to the aforesaid LK.
